parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the N20 engine can cause the vehicle to stall or shut down while driving, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine oil pressure light comes on
the vehicle stalls or shuts down
unusual noises or vibrations from the engine
excessive overheating
and metal shavings or debris in the engine oil.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain can cause the engine to stall or seize, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience a sudden loss of power
stalling
or engine seizure
accompanied by warning lights or messages on the dashboard
such as "Drive Train Malfunction" or "Low Engine Pressure".

stalling
or engine seizure
accompanied by warning lights or messages on the dashboard

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Oil Leaks and Filter Housing Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Oil leaks and filter housing failure can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience oil leaks
warning lights or messages on the dashboard
such as "Low Oil Pressure"
or engine noise and vibration.

stalling
or engine seizure
accompanied by warning lights or messages on the dashboard

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire failure can cause loss of control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded.

tire blowout

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of power and control, which can result in accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts off while driving
the fuel supply error message appears on the dashboard
the engine light comes on
the vehicle loses power and acceleration
the fuel pump module fails
and the vehicle may not restart.
